The paper deals with geometric operators and their coarsening, which are common topics in computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses algebraic multigrid techniques (cs.NA) and functional maps (cs.CG), which are relevant subfields. Additionally, the paper's applications include shape matching and graph pooling for convolutional neural networks, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS).
